Swiss National Bank Maintains Position in Continental Building Products, Inc. (CBPX)

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 

Swiss National Bank continued to hold its position in Continental Building Products, Inc. (NYSE:CBPX) during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the SEC. The institutional investor owned 67,100 shares of the construction company’s stock at the end of the first quarter. Swiss National Bank owned approximately 0.17% of Continental Building Products worth $1,644,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Several other hedge funds and other institutional investors also recently bought and sold shares of CBPX. Dimensional Fund Advisors LP raised its stake in shares of Continental Building Products by 10.9% in the fourth quarter. Dimensional Fund Advisors LP now owns 1,403,609 shares of the construction company’s stock valued at $32,424,000 after buying an additional 138,293 shares during the period. Macquarie Group Ltd. raised its stake in shares of Continental Building Products by 7.6% in the fourth quarter. Macquarie Group Ltd. now owns 1,264,205 shares of the construction company’s stock valued at $29,203,000 after buying an additional 88,828 shares during the period. Norges Bank acquired a new stake in shares of Continental Building Products during the fourth quarter valued at $830,000. American Century Companies Inc. raised its stake in shares of Continental Building Products by 5.7% in the first quarter. American Century Companies Inc. now owns 631,449 shares of the construction company’s stock valued at $15,471,000 after buying an additional 33,801 shares during the period. Finally, Highbridge Capital Management LLC acquired a new stake in shares of Continental Building Products during the fourth quarter valued at $774,000. Institutional investors own 97.65% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Continental Building Products Inc. alerts:



Continental Building Products, Inc. (NYSE:CBPX) traded down 0.68% on Friday, hitting $21.95. 202,004 shares of the stock traded hands. The stock has a 50-day moving average price of $23.46 and a 200 day moving average price of $23.99. The company has a market cap of $860.88 million, a price-to-earnings ratio of 20.16 and a beta of 1.31. Continental Building Products, Inc. has a 1-year low of $18.35 and a 1-year high of $26.52. 




Continental Building Products (NYSE:CBPX) last announced its earnings results on Thursday, May 4th. The construction company reported $0.32 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping the consensus estimate of $0.26 by $0.06. The business had revenue of $120.60 million for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $109.81 million. Continental Building Products had a return on equity of 15.57% and a net margin of 9.30%. The business’s revenue for the quarter was up 8.2% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period last year, the firm posted $0.30 earnings per share. On average, analysts anticipate that Continental Building Products, Inc. will post $1.36 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
