Separately, Zacks Investment Research upgraded Quanex Building Products Corporation from a “sell” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Friday, March 10th.
In other news, SVP Kevin P. Delaney sold 9,971 shares of the firm’s stock in a transaction dated Thursday, June 15th. The stock was sold at an average price of $21.53, for a total transaction of $214,675.63. Following the completion of the sale, the senior vice president now directly owns 113,442 shares in the company, valued at $2,442,406.26. The sale was disclosed in a legal filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which can be accessed through this hyperlink. Also, SVP Kevin P. Delaney sold 13,642 shares of the firm’s stock in a transaction dated Thursday, June 29th. The shares were sold at an average price of $21.01, for a total value of $286,618.42. Following the sale, the senior vice president now owns 111,991 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $2,352,930.91. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Insiders have sold 104,809 shares of company stock valued at $2,230,713 over the last 90 days. Insiders own  5.32% of the company’s stock. 
